                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Upper left corner: National Library modern ex libris. Lower right corner: remains of a red wax seal. </note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Middle of page in brown ink by a medieva hand: <quote xml:lang="la">probacio penne</quote>, <quote xml:lang="la">salue mater</quote> (pen-trials).</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> Red vax seal in lower right corner of left flyleaf. </p>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding>
                                <p> Contemporary binding. Brown or white leather over oak boards. 3 pairs of raised bands and endband. Strap and pin fastening, pin at the <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>. </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>, top in brown ink <quote>N 39</quote>; bottom stamped in gold: <quote>A 39</quote>; <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, brown ink on paper label: <quote>A 39</quote>. </p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="205" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="140" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="25" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>Leather dirty and torn. Boards visible on all sides. Worm holes all over. Bottom endband missing. Traces of nails (from chain staples) and rust on upper part of <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100102">Denmark</placeName>
                                </origPlace>
                                <origDate notAfter="1425" notBefore="1375">14th century, last quarter, or 15th century, first quarter</origDate>
                            </p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The manuscript belonged the library of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102535">Stephanus Johannis Stephanius</persName> (1599-1650). See <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107137">Jørgensen (1909–1911)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="771" to="773" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl> and <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107138">Jørgensen (1917)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="19" to="22" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>. From there it was sold to <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102549">Magnus Gabriel De la Gardie</persName> (his seal is found on LCI) and from him to <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100002">Uppsala University Library</orgName>. In <date when="1686"/> the manuscript was transferred to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100060">College of Antiquities</orgName> (later the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>), see <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107139">Annerstedt (1894)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="96" to="96" unit="page">Appendix 6:1</citedRange>
                                </bibl>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Current signum, <quote>A 39</quote>, first established in Helin’s catalogue from the 1720s (U 91:2:2).</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Also mentioned in the following catalogues and inventories: U 89, 3v; U 90:2, p. 14r, <quote>no. 202</quote>; U 91:3, <quote>no. 27</quote>; U 91:5, <quote>no XXII</quote>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p/>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>From the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName> to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> in <date when="1780"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
                    <additional>
                        <listBibl>
